00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:25.620 align:middle line:10%
Life Between Lives
therapy is a technique

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:28.560 align:middle line:10%
where you are
coming into a place

00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:30.210 align:middle line:10%
where you are able
to see your life

00:05:30.210 --> 00:05:32.490 align:middle line:10%
from an objective viewpoint.

00:05:32.490 --> 00:05:36.150 align:middle line:84%
So you're able to look at
your traumas, your situation,

00:05:36.150 --> 00:05:38.910 align:middle line:84%
your problem and put
them in a perspective.

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:42.240 align:middle line:84%
My original degree was in
psychology and philosophy.

00:05:42.240 --> 00:05:44.310 align:middle line:84%
And along the way,
I took degrees

00:05:44.310 --> 00:05:48.030 align:middle line:84%
at other places, New York
University, Columbia University.

00:05:48.030 --> 00:05:50.400 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point,
my eldest sister,

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:52.320 align:middle line:84%
who was studying
astrology, invited me

00:05:52.320 --> 00:05:54.000 align:middle line:90%
to her astrology class.

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:58.020 align:middle line:84%
And I went to her class
not believing in astrology.

00:05:58.020 --> 00:06:02.670 align:middle line:84%
There was a person who led us
to past lives spontaneously.

00:06:02.670 --> 00:06:06.810 align:middle line:84%
And I had what is called the
cinematic experience-- visual,

00:06:06.810 --> 00:06:09.520 align:middle line:90%
deep, profound, life-changing.

00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:11.610 align:middle line:84%
But at that point,
I just sort of

00:06:11.610 --> 00:06:13.960 align:middle line:84%
thought it was a very
creative experience,

00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:17.242 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't trust how
easily people sort of did it.

00:06:17.242 --> 00:06:18.950 align:middle line:84%
