comes up your higher mind's
guided us towards, but just

00:12:12.870 --> 00:12:14.080 align:middle line:90%
to have a list.

00:12:14.080 --> 00:12:14.880 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:14.880 --> 00:12:16.900 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that's sort
of the crux of it.

00:12:16.900 --> 00:12:17.700 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:20.320 align:middle line:84%
>> And how are you feeling
in this second right now,

00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:21.480 align:middle line:90%
in this moment?

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:22.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Curious.

00:12:22.730 --> 00:12:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Curious?

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:24.220 align:middle line:84%
>> To know what's
going to happen.

00:12:24.220 --> 00:12:24.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:12:24.630 --> 00:12:25.430 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:25.430 --> 00:12:33.350 align:middle line:90%


00:12:33.350 --> 00:12:37.130 align:middle line:84%
>> What are you feeling
or sensing right now?

00:12:37.130 --> 00:12:43.640 align:middle line:10%
>> It's a little wooden house,
like a children's house somehow.

00:12:43.640 --> 00:12:44.510 align:middle line:10%
>> Uh-huh.

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:46.200 align:middle line:10%
>> It's isolated.

00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:47.690 align:middle line:10%
>> It's isolated?

00:12:47.690 --> 00:12:49.550 align:middle line:10%
>> It's a bit dark.

00:12:49.550 --> 00:12:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>> And how does that make you
feel to be in this isolated,

00:12:52.310 --> 00:12:54.380 align:middle line:90%
a bit dark?

00:12:54.380 --> 00:12:59.350 align:middle line:10%
>> It's sort of got that
atmosphere of like a fairy tale.

00:12:59.350 --> 00:13:00.290 align:middle line:10%
And I don't know.

00:13:00.290 --> 00:13:03.010 align:middle line:10%
There's something a
bit ominous about it.

00:13:03.010 --> 00:13:03.810 align:middle line:10%
I don't know.

00:13:03.810 --> 00:13:07.070 align:middle line:10%
I just keep thinking something
like Hansel and Gretel.

00:13:07.070 --> 00:13:08.990 align:middle line:84%
In the very beginning,
it was fine.

00:13:08.990 --> 00:13:13.220 align:middle line:84%
But then it just, this
atmosphere took over,

00:13:13.220 --> 00:13:16.500 align:middle line:84%
and I was-- sort of started
absorbing the atmosphere.

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:21.860 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- there's something
ominous, something not OK here.

00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:25.380 align:middle line:10%
It's not quite what I--

00:13:25.380 --> 00:13:29.430 align:middle line:10%
I'd hoped for or
expected or something.

00:13:29.430 --> 00:13:31.720 align:middle line:10%
>> What did you expect?

00:13:31.720 --> 00:13:35.330 align:middle line:10%
>> Something brighter,
more sunshine, more happy.

00:13:35.330 --> 00:13:36.130 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:13:36.130 --> 00:13:38.840 align:middle line:84%
So here, she's
expressing expectation.

00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:41.170 align:middle line:84%
No matter how much we
try, even as therapists,

00:13:41.170 --> 00:13:43.730 align:middle line:84%
we can't get away
from expectations.

00:13:43.730 --> 00:13:45.310 align:middle line:84%
So for me, that she
was disappointed

00:13:45.310 --> 00:13:47.860 align:middle line:84%
was brilliant because it
meant we could work with it.

00:13:47.860 --> 00:13:50.300 align:middle line:10%
>> There's something
about abandonment there,

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:53.470 align:middle line:10%
and I feel abandoned.

00:13:53.470 --> 00:13:57.010 align:middle line:10%
It's not the sunshine
that I wanted.

00:13:57.010 --> 00:14:01.540 align:middle line:84%
>> So now that you know
this, what happens now?

00:14:01.540 --> 00:14:03.960 align:middle line:10%
>> Find people or
go somewhere else.

00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:04.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:04.990 --> 00:14:07.580 align:middle line:84%
So you have to find people
or go somewhere else?

00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:08.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:08.570 --> 00:14:09.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:14:09.370 --> 00:14:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And what do you do now to go
somewhere else or find people?

00:14:13.390 --> 00:14:14.872 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm going to the beach.

00:14:14.872 --> 00:14:16.080 align:middle line:90%
>> You're going to the beach?

00:14:16.080 --> 00:14:16.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:16.900 --> 00:14:17.878 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:14:17.878 --> 00:14:19.420 align:middle line:84%
She wasn't comfortable
where she was,

00:14:19.420 --> 00:14:21.337 align:middle line:84%
so I realized she needed
to go somewhere else.

00:14:21.337 --> 00:14:23.350 align:middle line:84%
So I offered different
possibilities

00:14:23.350 --> 00:14:24.470 align:middle line:90%
of what she could do.

00:14:24.470 --> 00:14:27.430 align:middle line:84%
>> So then she asks me if I
wanted to go somewhere else.

00:14:27.430 --> 00:14:29.680 align:middle line:90%
And I shoom out like a shot.

00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:32.340 align:middle line:84%
>> How does it feel to
arrive to the beach?

00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:33.140 align:middle line:10%
>> It's good.

00:14:33.140 --> 00:14:35.500 align:middle line:10%
I just remember a
photo of my mother

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:38.040 align:middle line:10%
and me sitting on the beach.

00:14:38.040 --> 00:14:39.730 align:middle line:10%
I don't have any memory of it.

00:14:39.730 --> 00:14:47.190 align:middle line:10%
I just have a photo, but I'm
really feeling loved by her.

00:14:47.190 --> 00:14:49.560 align:middle line:10%
You know it makes me very happy.

00:14:49.560 --> 00:14:52.800 align:middle line:10%
So I think she was
really happy then too.

00:14:52.800 --> 00:14:55.680 align:middle line:84%
My mother died when I was
12, and I don't really

00:14:55.680 --> 00:15:01.990 align:middle line:84%
have memories of her hugging me
and really feeling loved by her.

00:15:01.990 --> 00:15:06.150 align:middle line:84%
It was just like this period
before we went to Australia.

00:15:06.150 --> 00:15:09.750 align:middle line:10%
And I felt as though it
was all sort of light.

00:15:09.750 --> 00:15:13.140 align:middle line:10%
You know I feel as though
they were sort of light years

00:15:13.140 --> 00:15:16.690 align:middle line:10%
before the darkness came.

00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:22.650 align:middle line:10%
I didn't have a burden
somehow to feel weighed down.

00:15:22.650 --> 00:15:24.220 align:middle line:10%
>> You didn't feel weighed down?

00:15:24.220 --> 00:15:25.595 align:middle line:10%
You didn't have a burden?

00:15:25.595 --> 00:15:30.030 align:middle line:10%
>> All this was in England
and before we immigrated

00:15:30.030 --> 00:15:32.000 align:middle line:10%
to Australia.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:35.000 align:middle line:10%
I remember it was a big
secret, and my father

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.790 align:middle line:10%
told me this secret.

00:15:37.790 --> 00:15:41.315 align:middle line:10%
And I was only
sort of about four.

00:15:41.315 --> 00:15:43.160 align:middle line:10%
>> It was a big secret?

00:15:43.160 --> 00:15:45.470 align:middle line:10%
>> That we were going to
go to live in Australia,

00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:47.116 align:middle line:10%
but I couldn't tell anybody.

00:15:47.116 --> 00:15:48.230 align:middle line:10%
>> Uh-huh.

00:15:48.230 --> 00:15:50.910 align:middle line:84%
>> My father tells
me, this is a secret.

00:15:50.910 --> 00:15:52.670 align:middle line:84%
You mustn't tell
anyone, but we're

00:15:52.670 --> 00:15:54.970 align:middle line:84%
going to go and
emigrate to Australia.

00:15:54.970 --> 00:16:01.970 align:middle line:84%
What I took on then is
his fear, his doubts.

00:16:01.970 --> 00:16:04.760 align:middle line:84%
God, if he's scared
about this big journey

00:16:04.760 --> 00:16:08.150 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to
take, what about me?

00:16:08.150 --> 00:16:09.710 align:middle line:10%
And then we went to Australia.

00:16:09.710 --> 00:16:12.060 align:middle line:10%
And then we didn't
have any family.

00:16:12.060 --> 00:16:12.920 align:middle line:10%
Nobody.

00:16:12.920 --> 00:16:14.720 align:middle line:10%
Didn't know anybody.

00:16:14.720 --> 00:16:18.260 align:middle line:10%
And I think it was that
first sort of setting up

00:16:18.260 --> 00:16:22.160 align:middle line:10%
that pattern for
me of being cut off

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:26.630 align:middle line:10%
from roots and
family and my mother

00:16:26.630 --> 00:16:31.040 align:middle line:10%
then being sick in
Australia and the change.

00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:33.855 align:middle line:10%
I think it sort of then
became the dark years

00:16:33.855 --> 00:16:37.340 align:middle line:10%
you know with the family.

00:16:37.340 --> 00:16:46.100 align:middle line:10%
I can't remember her sort of
ever kissing me or affection.

00:16:46.100 --> 00:16:49.100 align:middle line:10%
You know I've always sort of
thought of it more as my mother

00:16:49.100 --> 00:16:52.490 align:middle line:10%
died, but it was really that--

00:16:52.490 --> 00:16:54.920 align:middle line:10%
>> Moving to Australia
and keeping the secret,

00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:56.040 align:middle line:10%
it being a secret even?

00:16:56.040 --> 00:16:56.840 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:16:56.840 --> 00:16:57.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:16:57.870 --> 00:16:59.940 align:middle line:10%
>> I think 'cause I
was just very young,

00:16:59.940 --> 00:17:05.560 align:middle line:10%
I haven't ever felt the
emotional impact of that on me.

00:17:05.560 --> 00:17:06.619 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:17:06.619 --> 00:17:08.990 align:middle line:84%
She steps into this
revelation about her father

00:17:08.990 --> 00:17:10.819 align:middle line:84%
where she suddenly
understands it's not

00:17:10.819 --> 00:17:12.530 align:middle line:84%
just that she was
keeping a secret

00:17:12.530 --> 00:17:17.119 align:middle line:84%
but that she was picking up on
all of his own emotional fauna

00:17:17.119 --> 00:17:18.270 align:middle line:90%
and his fears.

00:17:18.270 --> 00:17:20.599 align:middle line:84%
And this for her was very
overwhelming and frightening,

00:17:20.599 --> 00:17:22.849 align:middle line:84%
which then led to her
basic theme, which

00:17:22.849 --> 00:17:26.300 align:middle line:84%
is the theme of losing the
family, of grief, of not having

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:28.620 align:middle line:84%
what she needs, of
being disappointed.

00:17:28.620 --> 00:17:31.740 align:middle line:10%
>> Just seems like
too much emotion.

00:17:31.740 --> 00:17:33.280 align:middle line:10%
>> There's too much emotion?

00:17:33.280 --> 00:17:34.710 align:middle line:10%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:17:34.710 --> 00:17:38.070 align:middle line:10%
>> And what happens when
there's too much emotion?

00:17:38.070 --> 00:17:41.290 align:middle line:10%
>> I have to tune out.

00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:42.090 align:middle line:10%
>> Uh-huh.

00:17:42.090 --> 00:17:45.630 align:middle line:84%
You have to tune out when
there's too much emotion.

00:17:45.630 --> 00:17:47.800 align:middle line:84%
And when you tune
out, where do you go?

00:17:47.800 --> 00:17:49.270 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:17:49.270 --> 00:17:50.590 align:middle line:10%
>> I sleep.

00:17:50.590 --> 00:17:51.500 align:middle line:90%
>> You sleep?

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:52.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:17:52.330 --> 00:17:53.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:17:53.160 --> 00:17:56.480 align:middle line:84%
And when you sleep,
what happens?

00:17:56.480 --> 00:18:00.020 align:middle line:10%
>> Then I can go and
dream and go anywhere.

00:18:00.020 --> 00:18:03.050 align:middle line:84%
>> That's one of her themes,
is that she is very influenced

00:18:03.050 --> 00:18:06.530 align:middle line:84%
by other people's emotions,
and it can be overwhelming.

00:18:06.530 --> 00:18:08.840 align:middle line:84%
She uses sleep to
regenerate her body.

00:18:08.840 --> 00:18:12.020 align:middle line:84%
She uses sleep to
become more clear.

00:18:12.020 --> 00:18:14.660 align:middle line:90%
And she uses it also to heal.

00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:18.110 align:middle line:10%
>> Feels just like
going to the stars,

00:18:18.110 --> 00:18:25.010 align:middle line:10%
just going out into nothingness.

00:18:25.010 --> 00:18:26.405 align:middle line:10%
Space.

00:18:26.405 --> 00:18:29.090 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're added to
the stars and to space.

00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:30.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:18:30.950 --> 00:18:33.641 align:middle line:10%
Ultimate freedom.

00:18:33.641 --> 00:18:38.630 align:middle line:84%
It's like this limitlessness,
this feeling of one

00:18:38.630 --> 00:18:43.550 align:middle line:84%
with whatever is but you
haven't got all of this drama.

00:18:43.550 --> 00:18:44.660 align:middle line:90%
It's just free.

00:18:44.660 --> 00:18:46.700 align:middle line:90%
It's flying free.

00:18:46.700 --> 00:18:48.020 align:middle line:10%
It's dissolving now.

00:18:48.020 --> 00:18:53.720 align:middle line:10%
I just feel as though I'm
coming back into sleep.

00:18:53.720 --> 00:18:55.550 align:middle line:10%
>> And how does that feel?

00:18:55.550 --> 00:18:58.350 align:middle line:10%
>> In my body now, not in this--

00:18:58.350 --> 00:19:00.080 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah, in the space.

00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:03.710 align:middle line:10%
>> In that space of
being with no body.

00:19:03.710 --> 00:19:07.640 align:middle line:84%
Would it be useful to
go further back in time?

00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:12.060 align:middle line:84%
Or is there anywhere else
you need to go first?

00:19:12.060 --> 00:19:12.990 align:middle line:90%
What's happening now?

00:19:12.990 --> 00:19:15.540 align:middle line:10%
>> No, I was just
thinking of Dora again,

00:19:15.540 --> 00:19:18.590 align:middle line:10%
just something about--

00:19:18.590 --> 00:19:22.770 align:middle line:10%
you know, when you say, is there
anything else, any other place

00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:26.120 align:middle line:10%
you need to go, I just
immediately thought,

00:19:26.120 --> 00:19:27.010 align:middle line:10%
I don't know.

00:19:27.010 --> 00:19:27.810 align:middle line:10%
>> Uh-huh.

00:19:27.810 --> 00:19:28.610 align:middle line:10%
And so--

00:19:28.610 --> 00:19:29.660 align:middle line:10%
>> Just Dora.

00:19:29.660 --> 00:19:30.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:33.300 align:middle line:84%
So if you need to go to Dora,
let's see what happens, OK?

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:35.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:38.090 align:middle line:10%
I'm sorry if I've
caused her any pain.

00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:41.042 align:middle line:10%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:19:41.042 --> 00:19:47.170 align:middle line:10%
>> Or if any of my
actions have hurt her or--

00:19:47.170 --> 00:19:49.810 align:middle line:10%
it just weighs on me that--

00:19:49.810 --> 00:19:52.621 align:middle line:10%
I haven't wanted
to hurt you or--

00:19:52.621 --> 00:19:54.345 align:middle line:10%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:19:54.345 --> 00:19:59.150 align:middle line:10%
>> And I tried so
hard, I tried so hard.

00:19:59.150 --> 00:20:02.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, you tried so hard.

00:20:02.650 --> 00:20:03.896 align:middle line:90%
>> [SNIFFLES]

00:20:03.896 --> 00:20:06.890 align:middle line:90%


00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:09.650 align:middle line:84%
I just have felt
this remorse that we

00:20:09.650 --> 00:20:13.500 align:middle line:84%
couldn't clear up a couple of
misunderstandings that we had.

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And I felt that there was a
little bit of lack of trust

00:20:16.730 --> 00:20:19.200 align:middle line:90%
and that we hadn't gone into it.

00:20:19.200 --> 00:20:22.353 align:middle line:84%
And then she just very
suddenly, abruptly dies.

00:20:22.353 --> 00:20:25.770 align:middle line:90%


00:20:25.770 --> 00:20:27.990 align:middle line:10%
I feel she's here.

00:20:27.990 --> 00:20:30.444 align:middle line:10%
>> You feel she's there?

00:20:30.444 --> 00:20:34.030 align:middle line:10%
>> She's telling me it's OK.

00:20:34.030 --> 00:20:38.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Instead of me saving her,
instead of thinking of solutions

00:20:38.350 --> 00:20:41.360 align:middle line:84%
to make her feel better,
Dora came on her own.

00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:43.180 align:middle line:84%
And for me, that was
extremely important

00:20:43.180 --> 00:20:45.110 align:middle line:84%
because it wasn't
something contrived.

00:20:45.110 --> 00:20:46.840 align:middle line:90%
It was natural.

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:48.410 align:middle line:90%
Take all the time you need.

00:20:48.410 --> 00:20:51.260 align:middle line:90%


00:20:51.260 --> 00:20:53.846 align:middle line:10%
>> She said it's all OK.

00:20:53.846 --> 00:20:56.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:20:56.140 --> 00:20:57.640 align:middle line:90%
So she's speaking with you?

00:20:57.640 --> 00:21:03.490 align:middle line:90%


00:21:03.490 --> 00:21:09.610 align:middle line:84%
>> The OK-ness was that I could
just see her totally OK and big

00:21:09.610 --> 00:21:15.730 align:middle line:84%
smile and happy and certainly
not holding on to something like

00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:17.020 align:middle line:90%
I am.

00:21:17.020 --> 00:21:20.590 align:middle line:10%
No, I felt my heart warm.

00:21:20.590 --> 00:21:22.130 align:middle line:90%
>> You felt your heart warm?

00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:25.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:21:25.630 --> 00:21:27.830 align:middle line:10%
No, I'm not--
she's not here now.

00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:30.130 align:middle line:10%
I don't feel that she's--

00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:34.540 align:middle line:10%
but when she was here, I
felt it go to my heart.

00:21:34.540 --> 00:21:36.805 align:middle line:10%
And she told me she loved me.

00:21:36.805 --> 00:21:39.090 align:middle line:10%
She never told me that before.

00:21:39.090 --> 00:21:40.750 align:middle line:10%
>> She never told you?

00:21:40.750 --> 00:21:46.510 align:middle line:10%
>> I told her that I loved her,
but she'd never said it to me.

00:21:46.510 --> 00:21:48.610 align:middle line:90%
>> She'd never said it to you?

00:21:48.610 --> 00:21:52.300 align:middle line:90%
And now she has.

00:21:52.300 --> 00:21:55.010 align:middle line:90%
Dora says to her, I love you.

00:21:55.010 --> 00:21:57.220 align:middle line:84%
Now you have to
remember, her mother

00:21:57.220 --> 00:22:00.740 align:middle line:84%
never expressed
emotion and affection.

00:22:00.740 --> 00:22:02.430 align:middle line:90%
And she speaks about this.

00:22:02.430 --> 00:22:04.730 align:middle line:90%
Dora was her dear friend.

00:22:04.730 --> 00:22:06.380 align:middle line:90%
It was a brilliant friendship.

00:22:06.380 --> 00:22:08.600 align:middle line:84%
But she had said I
love you to Dora.

00:22:08.600 --> 00:22:10.400 align:middle line:90%
Dora never said I love you back.

00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:12.070 align:middle line:84%
We know that Dora
said it was OK.

00:22:12.070 --> 00:22:15.230 align:middle line:84%
And that immediately shifted
something in her body.

00:22:15.230 --> 00:22:17.530 align:middle line:84%
Her whole body, if
you really study it,

00:22:17.530 --> 00:22:20.770 align:middle line:84%
relaxed because she's been
carrying this as a tension,

00:22:20.770 --> 00:22:24.010 align:middle line:84%
because this has
been massive for her.

00:22:24.010 --> 00:22:28.420 align:middle line:84%
Is there any place you need to
